00:37:09,269 --> 00:37:11,020
I'm a little slow.

495
00:37:13,481 --> 00:37:15,608
Take your time.

496
00:37:15,692 --> 00:37:20,029
I'm trying to look as pretty as you,
which I'm convinced I can.

497
00:37:22,073 --> 00:37:24,617
It just takes me a little longer.

498
00:37:25,702 --> 00:37:27,161
You got anything to munch on?

499
00:37:27,245 --> 00:37:31,081
Yeah, there's a thing full of stuff
next to the fridge.

500
00:37:31,166 --> 00:37:35,169
It's got a lock on it.
Use that key from the ring I gave you.

501
00:37:44,179 --> 00:37:45,846
Do you see it?

502
00:37:45,931 --> 00:37:47,348
Yeah, sure.

503
00:37:59,527 --> 00:38:01,362
You find something?

504
00:38:07,369 --> 00:38:12,206
Listen, Capps is a tough guy,
but he's also a blowhard.

505
00:38:13,583 --> 00:38:15,876
He loves to give the impression
that he's connected.

506
00:38:16,878 --> 00:38:18,504
Thinks it's glamorous.

507
00:38:21,216 --> 00:38:23,550
He said a couple of things.

508
00:38:27,806 --> 00:38:30,474
Hey, you're about to take the bar exam.

509
00:38:31,184 --> 00:38:33,394
Here's a multiple choice.

510
00:38:33,770 --> 00:38:36,522
The difference between
tax avoidance and tax evasion is...

511
00:38:37,357 --> 00:38:40,484
A, whatever the IRS says.

512
00:38:41,820 --> 00:38:44,488
B, a smart lawyer.

513
00:38:45,407 --> 00:38:48,826
C, 10 years in prison.

514
00:38:48,910 --> 00:38:51,495
D, all of the above.

515
00:38:52,330 --> 00:38:55,332
Being a tax lawyer's
got nothing to do with the law.

516
00:38:55,417 --> 00:38:57,084
It's a game.

517
00:38:57,210 --> 00:38:59,003
We teach the rich how to play it,

518
00:38:59,087 --> 00:39:00,713
so they can stay rich.

519
00:39:01,548 --> 00:39:04,091
The IRS keeps changing the rules

520
00:39:04,217 --> 00:39:07,094
so we can keep getting rich
teaching them.

521
00:39:07,178 --> 00:39:10,681
It's a game.
One you just played very, very well.

522
00:39:10,765 --> 00:39:12,683
Where's your beer?

523
00:39:12,767 --> 00:39:15,102
I decided to wait for the rum.
I hear it's good down here.

524
00:39:15,186 --> 00:39:17,771
Everything's good down here.
You deserve a taste of all of it.

525
00:39:34,956 --> 00:39:37,207
I think that
since we're here on this island,

526
00:39:37,292 --> 00:39:41,211
there's things we can do on it,
you know, primitive things.

527
00:39:41,921 --> 00:39:43,964
Come on, you deserve it.

528
00:39:48,470 --> 00:39:52,222
Look, I don't mean to hurt your feelings,
but this isn't gonna happen.

529
00:39:52,307 --> 00:39:54,475
Would you tell my friend
I went back to the condo?

530
00:39:54,601 --> 00:39:57,227
You don't know what you're missing.

531
00:39:58,897 --> 00:40:00,481
Thanks anyway.

532
00:40:25,924 --> 00:40:27,466
- Leave me alone!
- Listen to me.

533
00:40:53,034 --> 00:40:54,118
Are you all right?

534
00:40:54,202 --> 00:40:57,329
It's okay. Just wait a minute.

535
00:40:59,749 --> 00:41:01,041
Wait a minute.

536
00:41:01,835 --> 00:41:04,002
Can I look at this?

537
00:41:04,087 --> 00:41:05,963
You're not a doctor.

538
00:41:06,047 --> 00:41:08,924
No, but I've

539
00:41:09,050 --> 00:41:12,386
sprained a lot of ankles.

540
00:41:13,888 --> 00:41:15,514
Mostly mine.

541
00:41:21,604 --> 00:41:25,065
You should ice this.

542
00:41:25,733 --> 00:41:27,526
You should also report that guy.

543
00:41:34,576 --> 00:41:36,702
That was your boyfriend.

544
00:41:39,789 --> 00:41:41,582
That was for money.

545
00:41:52,969 --> 00:41:56,096
- Aren't you gonna finish?
- I'm sorry.

546
00:42:00,602 --> 00:42:03,896
- You think that's...
- Got nothing to do with me.

547
00:42:10,778 --> 00:42:13,405
- Is this too tight?
- No.

548
00:42:19,078 --> 00:42:21,163
I work in a travel agency.

549
00:42:28,338 --> 00:42:32,257
I wanted to feel like all those people

550
00:42:35,136 --> 00:42:38,138
with first class tickets
and pretty clothes.

551
00:42:42,810 --> 00:42:46,313
I guess I wanted to feel...

552
00:42:48,983 --> 00:42:50,359
Rich.

553
00:43:01,663 --> 00:43:04,331
How much would it take to feel rich?

554
00:43:05,041 --> 00:43:06,541
I don't know.

555
00:43:11,881 --> 00:43:14,508
How much would it take to feel safe?

556
00:43:25,186 --> 00:43:26,687
You did that.

557
00:43:31,234 --> 00:43:33,235
You made me feel safe.

558
00:43:54,716 --> 00:43:56,049
Hey...

559
00:44:16,738 --> 00:44:19,323
Will you stay with me for a while?

560
00:45:47,995 --> 00:45:51,665
Why don't you take the afternoon off?
You deserve it.

561
00:45:51,749 --> 00:45:53,708
Spend it with that pretty wife of yours.

562
00:45:53,835 --> 00:45:56,837
Oh, shit, I forgot, she phoned last night.

563
00:45:58,005 --> 00:45:59,840
What'd you tell her?

564
00:45:59,924 --> 00:46:02,717
That you were probably
walking on the beach.

565
00:46:02,844 --> 00:46:03,927
I was.

566
00:46:04,011 --> 00:46:06,263
I guessed right then, didn't I?

567
00:46:10,935 --> 00:46:15,856
Okay, Mr. McDeere.
If you'll sign where the "X" is

568
00:46:15,940 --> 00:46:18,358
and initial where it's marked.

569
00:46:39,672 --> 00:46:43,425
Well, well.
The man from Gentleman's Quarterly.

570
00:46:44,594 --> 00:46:46,595
How you doing, Ray?

571
00:46:46,679 --> 00:46:49,389
Pretty fair. How's yourself?

572
00:46:54,479 --> 00:46:56,855
It's a long time, huh?

573
00:46:56,939 --> 00:47:00,400
It's okay. I've become a patient man.

574
00:47:05,740 --> 00:47:08,116
Don't beat yourself up, kid.

575
00:47:08,201 --> 00:47:11,703
If I wasn't here,
I wouldn't want to be here either.

576
00:47:20,046 --> 00:47:23,381
- Do you ever talk to Ma?
- A few months ago.

577
00:47:26,511 --> 00:47:29,971
- Still with the same guy?
- They're all the same guy.

578
00:47:35,603 --> 00:47:39,606
So, you finish law school?

579
00:47:40,650 --> 00:47:41,775
Yeah.

580
00:47:43,027 --> 00:47:45,278
That suit's a dead give-away.

581
00:47:46,739 --> 00:47:48,907
What, you get a job on Wall Street?

582
00:47:48,991 --> 00:47:51,910
- You always said...
- No, I'm not. I just...

583
00:47:54,247 --> 00:47:57,165
I went with a firm across the river
in Memphis.

584
00:47:57,250 --> 00:47:58,667
Memphis?

585
00:47:58,751 --> 00:48:00,252
Hey, Ray,

586
00:48:01,254 --> 00:48:03,880
wouldn't it be funny
if I went to Harvard and you went to jail

587
00:48:03,965 --> 00:48:06,883
and we both ended up
surrounded by crooks?

588
00:48:09,804 --> 00:48:13,056
Sonny Capps is thrilled.
McDeere was dazzling.

589
00:48:13,140 --> 00:48:15,725
I think we ought to pull Lamar
out of that tax seminar in Washington

590
00:48:15,810 --> 00:48:17,477
and send Mitch instead.

591
00:48:17,562 --> 00:48:20,355
Let him take the jet.
Any problem with that, Bill?

592
00:48:20,439 --> 00:48:22,899
No. No, no problem.

593
00:48:22,984 --> 00:48:25,235
So far the kid's been real predictable.

594
00:48:26,529 --> 00:48:30,782
If you're even half right, you're gonna
need some help. What does Abby think?

595
00:48:32,034 --> 00:48:33,827
I haven't told her.

596
00:48:37,039 --> 00:48:38,623
I guess...

597
00:48:40,334 --> 00:48:42,961
I guess I don't want it to be real.

598
00:48:43,838 --> 00:48:46,256
Nothing's real until I tell it to Abby.

599
00:48:48,050 --> 00:48:51,761
How did you ever land a job
with a brother in the joint?

600
00:49:04,900 --> 00:49:08,194
That's okay.
I'd have done the same thing myself.

601
00:49:11,032 --> 00:49:15,452
You were always around for me, Ray.
All those years after Dad died.

602
00:49:15,536 --> 00:49:17,621
I'd have done the same.

603
00:49:17,705 --> 00:49:22,083
You think I'd ever tell guys around here
I got a brother in Harvard?

604
00:49:23,502 --> 00:49:25,211
Jesus, Ray.

605
00:49:25,296 --> 00:49:28,131
Hey, listen.
I want you to see a friend of mine.

606
00:49:29,050 --> 00:49:32,260
His name is Eddie Lomax.
He's a private investigator in Little Rock.

607
00:49:32,345 --> 00:49:33,595
Ex-cop.

608
00:49:34,555 --> 00:49:36,264
Anything I can do for you?

609
00:49:36,349 --> 00:49:38,475
Sure. Get me out of here.

610
00:49:41,103 --> 00:49:42,854
Where to?

611
00:49:44,440 --> 00:49:47,233
Anywhere I can see a whole lot of sky.

612
00:49:48,194 --> 00:49:51,446
I can get through the days,
I even eat the food.

613
00:49:52,281 --> 00:49:54,658
It's amazing
how much you miss the sky.

614
00:50:04,794 --> 00:50:08,171
Ever plug one of these in
only you forgot to put the water in?

615
00:50:08,255 --> 00:50:09,381
No.

616
00:50:10,132 --> 00:50:12,967
- Do you know what happens?
- No.

617
00:50:13,052 --> 00:50:14,803
The lights go out.

618
00:50:19,975 --> 00:50:22,185
He's been dying to see you
since you called.

619
00:50:22,269 --> 00:50:24,437
That's what I saw. Tammy!

620
00:50:26,148 --> 00:50:28,191
Mr. Lomax will see you now.

621
00:50:31,070 --> 00:50:32,195
- Mr. McDeere.
- Yes.

622
00:50:32,279 --> 00:50:34,155
I practically went to law school with you.

623
00:50:34,240 --> 00:50:37,784
Ray talked about you
every stinking day for three years.

624
00:50:37,868 --> 00:50:39,619
I was his cellmate,
he must have told you.

625
00:50:39,704 --> 00:50:42,038
Did he tell you,
by the way, it was statutory rape?

626
00:50:42,123 --> 00:50:45,166
She was 17. Looked 25.
I got one to four.

627
00:50:45,251 --> 00:50:48,211
Sit down. Sit down. Come on. Sit down,
sit down. You want some Sweet'N Low?

628
00:50:48,295 --> 00:50:49,379
- You want some dairy cream?
- No.

629
00:50:49,463 --> 00:50:50,922
You want some sugar?
You want some...

630
00:50:51,006 --> 00:50:52,382
Eddie, I've got some business

631
00:50:52,466 --> 00:50:54,050
- I'd like to go over with you here.
- Good. Good. Good.

632
00:50:54,135 --> 00:50:55,218
I owe your brother my life.

633
00:50:55,302 --> 00:50:57,721
- I'm leaving.
- Thank you, dear.

634
00:50:59,056 --> 00:51:00,974
That's my secretary. She is terrific.

635
00:51:01,058 --> 00:51:03,810
But she's got a nutcase for a husband.
He's a truck driver.

636
00:51:03,894 --> 00:51:05,770
He moved here
to be close to Graceland.

637
00:51:05,855 --> 00:51:07,147
The reason why, he thinks he's Elvis.

638
00:51:07,231 --> 00:51:11,401
What do you think his name is?
It's Elvis. Elvis Aaron Hemphill.

639
00:51:11,485 --> 00:51:13,403
I run across some strange things
in this job.

640
00:51:13,487 --> 00:51:16,781
Some things I'd never spray-paint
on an overpass.

641
00:51:18,325 --> 00:51:20,785
Now, what can I do for you?

642
00:51:22,955 --> 00:51:25,957
- What a nice surprise.
- Avery.

643
00:51:27,752 --> 00:51:30,587
They didn't have to disturb you.
You didn't have to come down.

644
00:51:30,671 --> 00:51:32,172
Believe me, it's no bother.

645
00:51:32,256 --> 00:51:33,298
I was just looking for Mitch.

646
00:51:33,382 --> 00:51:36,634
Nina says
he hasn't been in all afternoon.

647
00:51:36,719 --> 00:51:39,262
I didn't mean for her to call you.

648
00:51:40,890 --> 00:51:42,515
Didn't he come back with you?

649
00:51:42,600 --> 00:51:46,394
I'll be honest with you.
This is not my area of expertise.

650
00:51:47,396 --> 00:51:51,232
- But you think it's possible?
- Anything's possible.

651
00:51:51,317 --> 00:51:54,569
I'll tell you one thing, if those guys
at the steak joint were feds,

652
00:51:54,653 --> 00:51:55,904
you better watch out for them.

653
00:51:55,988 --> 00:51:59,032
'Cause they don't give a damn
about you.

654
00:51:59,116 --> 00:52:02,035
I get some pretty pissed off
husbands in here.

655
00:52:03,037 --> 00:52:07,624
On the other hand, the lawyers at your
firm sure as hell seem accident prone.

656
00:52:09,168 --> 00:52:10,335
Okay.

657
00:52:12,087 --> 00:52:14,380
I'll see what I can find out.

658
00:52:15,466 --> 00:52:17,717
You better let me call you.

659
00:52:21,055 --> 00:52:23,640
You sure remind me of your brother.

660
00:52:25,601 --> 00:52:28,061
Ray comes up for parole in a while.

661
00:52:28,979 --> 00:52:31,981
Says that he can last it.

662
00:52:32,441 --> 00:52:34,234
What do you think?

663
00:52:36,987 --> 00:52:40,573
There's guys that can do
all the hard time the State gives them.

664
00:52:40,658 --> 00:52:43,993
Whatever Ray had,
he used up to get this far.

665
00:52:53,337 --> 00:52:54,754
- Hi.
- Hi.

666
00:52:56,006 --> 00:52:58,466
- I didn't think you were home.
- Why not?

667
00:52:58,551 --> 00:53:01,177
- No car.
- I took it in for service.

668
00:53:02,137 --> 00:53:04,097
Avery brought me home.

669
00:53:06,016 --> 00:53:09,102
I went to the office looking for you.

670
00:53:09,186 --> 00:53:10,478
I wasn't there.

671
00:53:10,563 --> 00:53:13,273
Apparently not.
I even looked under your desk.

672
00:53:14,316 --> 00:53:16,985
- Yeah, I went...
- Avery told me you were at MSU,

673
00:53:17,069 --> 00:53:18,820
at the law library.

674
00:53:18,904 --> 00:53:20,363
- Avery did.
- Avery did.

675
00:53:20,447 --> 00:53:22,782
But when I happened to
spot your car in the parking lot,

676
00:53:22,867 --> 00:53:25,201
it made him kind of edgy.

677
00:53:25,286 --> 00:53:28,621
Yeah, well,
Avery didn't exactly know where I was.

678
00:53:30,165 --> 00:53:33,293
Probably thought
you were with another woman.

679
00:53:39,717 --> 00:53:41,509
I went to see Ray.

680
00:53:43,470 --> 00:53:44,721
Ray?

681
00:53:46,932 --> 00:53:49,851
- Yeah.
- Just like that, after all this time?

682
00:53:50,895 --> 00:53:52,979
You were right. I've been stupid.

683
00:53:55,900 --> 00:53:58,234
I would have gone with you on Saturday.

684
00:53:58,319 --> 00:54:01,696
I know. God, I just wasn't...
I wasn't thinking.

685
00:54:07,286 --> 00:54:08,745
How'd it go?

686
00:54:09,705 --> 00:54:14,834
It was...

687
00:54:15,377 --> 00:54:19,422
God, he...
He tried to make it easy for me.

688
00:54:21,383 --> 00:54:23,176
Is he okay?

689
00:54:25,137 --> 00:54:27,305
He's gotta get that parole.

690
00:54:32,686 --> 00:54:35,063
You want to try something?

691
00:54:35,147 --> 00:54:36,940
Let's put the books away,

692
00:54:37,024 --> 00:54:40,693
pretend we're back
in our old beat-up apartment, broke,

693
00:54:40,778 --> 00:54:43,905
and we find some money
we forgot in pockets.

694
00:54:45,950 --> 00:54:49,327
- We'll send out for pizza and drink beer.
- Drink beer.

695
00:54:51,622 --> 00:54:53,498
And watch Star Search.

696
00:54:55,376 --> 00:54:57,669
Who knows where it will lead.

697
00:55:20,776 --> 00:55:22,110
Your wife?

698
00:55:22,194 --> 00:55:24,737
- She's in Cleveland.
- She lies.

699
00:55:29,493 --> 00:55:31,828
Don't you answer your phone?

700
00:55:32,663 --> 00:55:34,831
Don't you knock?

701
00:55:34,915 --> 00:55:37,041
Where's your secretary?

702
00:55:39,628 --> 00:55:41,087
Out.

703
00:55:41,171 --> 00:55:44,674
- She left a cigarette burning.
- She does that.

704
00:55:44,758 --> 00:55:48,594
Why don't you come back in one hour,
and make an appointment?

705
00:55:48,679 --> 00:55:50,471
Why bother? We're here.

706
00:55:50,556 --> 00:55:52,056
I'm busy.

707
00:55:52,725 --> 00:55:54,726
Doing what?

708
00:55:54,810 --> 00:55:56,811
I'm getting a pedicure.

709
00:55:57,813 --> 00:55:59,564
What's it to you?

710
00:56:05,654 --> 00:56:08,823
Now this is gonna turn out badly for you,

711
00:56:08,907 --> 00:56:10,575
but we can make it relatively painless.

712
00:56:10,659 --> 00:56:14,245
Why are you asking questions
about dead lawyers?

713
00:56:14,329 --> 00:56:16,039
What dead lawyers?

714
00:56:19,752 --> 00:56:21,836
Who hired you to do that?

715
00:56:25,007 --> 00:56:27,800
Okay! Okay.

716
00:56:31,680 --> 00:56:33,473
Just let me think.

717
00:56:34,892 --> 00:56:38,895
His name was Julio Iglesias.

718
00:56:42,357 --> 00:56:44,025
No! No!

719
00:56:46,904 --> 00:56:48,154
Great!

720
00:56:48,906 --> 00:56:50,823
Just great.

721
00:56:50,908 --> 00:56:53,785
You want to ask him
a few questions now?

722
00:57:24,817 --> 00:57:27,360
I think
this is a carefully balanced proposal.

723
00:57:27,444 --> 00:57:30,738
I think it's high-minded
and I think it's fair-minded.

724
00:57:30,823 --> 00:57:34,283
In other words, it's got something in it
to offend everyone.

725
00:57:35,285 --> 00:57:36,536
If you want to follow along with me,

726
00:57:36,620 --> 00:57:39,705
we'll begin on page "l"
of the introduction.

727
00:57:40,624 --> 00:57:45,419
We'll revue sections 704-B
of the IRS code of 1986

728
00:57:45,504 --> 00:57:50,133
and the treasury regulations
amended under Section 1/704-1.

729
00:57:50,634 --> 00:57:52,510
Quote, "The distribution provisions

730
00:57:52,594 --> 00:57:54,929
"in limited and
general partnership agreements."

731
00:57:55,305 --> 00:57:59,058
These regulations permit the IRS to
disregard allocations

732
00:57:59,560 --> 00:58:01,060
which are not made in accordance

733
00:58:01,145 --> 00:58:03,396
with partners' interests
in the partnership

734
00:58:03,480 --> 00:58:06,899
unless those allocations
satisfy the economic effect

735
00:58:06,984 --> 00:58:08,860
most easily satisfied

736
00:58:08,944 --> 00:58:12,613
by taking advantage of the safe
harbor provisions set forth therein.

737
00:58:12,698 --> 00:58:16,159
In other words,
in an ever-changing sea of tax laws...

738
00:58:24,668 --> 00:58:26,043
Hey, brother.

739
00:58:29,173 --> 00:58:32,675
Brother, go down the steps
towards the pool.

740
00:58:32,759 --> 00:58:34,844
Here you go, brother.

741
00:58:36,096 --> 00:58:38,431
- Voices from the Wall.
- Thanks a lot.

742
00:58:38,515 --> 00:58:39,640
Oh, yeah.

743
00:58:39,725 --> 00:58:40,850
Mister.

744
00:58:53,197 --> 00:58:54,822
Who killed Eddie Lomax?

745
00:58:54,907 --> 00:58:58,034
Go over and sit next to
the man on the bench.

746
00:59:16,470 --> 00:59:19,096
I appreciate your coming, Mr. McDeere.

747
00:59:19,181 --> 00:59:21,557
I'll call you Mitch, if I may?

748
00:59:22,517 --> 00:59:25,186
My name is Voyles. Denton Voyles.

749
00:59:25,270 --> 00:59:26,854
I'm with the Department of Justice.

750
00:59:26,939 --> 00:59:29,232
What happened to Eddie Lomax?

751
00:59:29,942 --> 00:59:34,111
We've been investigating
Bendini, Lambert & Locke for four years.

752
00:59:35,030 --> 00:59:38,032
No lawyer has ever
left your law firm alive.

753
00:59:39,660 --> 00:59:41,869
Two tried to leave, they were killed.

754
00:59:41,954 --> 00:59:45,122
Two were about to try,
you know what happened.

755
00:59:46,208 --> 00:59:49,418
Now, we have reason to believe
that your house is bugged.

756
00:59:49,503 --> 00:59:53,089
Your phones are tapped,
your office is wired.

757
00:59:53,715 --> 00:59:57,885
They may follow you, they may be here
in Washington as we speak.

758
01:00:02,766 --> 01:00:04,225
Are you saying my life is in danger?

759
01:00:04,309 --> 01:00:07,520
I'm saying that
your life as you know it is over.

760
01:00:11,608 --> 01:00:14,151
Your law firm
is the sole legal representative

761
01:00:14,236 --> 01:00:16,696
of the Morolto crime family in Chicago.

762
01:00:16,780 --> 01:00:18,990
Known as the Mafia. The Mob.

763
01:00:21,451 --> 01:00:22,576
I don't believe it.

764
01:00:22,661 --> 01:00:24,161
They set up legitimate businesses

765
01:00:24,246 --> 01:00:27,957
with dirty money from drugs,
gambling, prostitution.

766
01:00:28,041 --> 01:00:31,627
All cash, all moved offshore.
You believe it.

767
01:00:31,712 --> 01:00:34,463
That's why you talked
to Thomas Abanks in the Caymans.

768
01:00:34,548 --> 01:00:36,382
That's why you got
this private investigator

769
01:00:36,466 --> 01:00:39,510
asking questions that got him killed.

770
01:00:40,887 --> 01:00:44,473
Maybe 30% of their clients
are legitimate.

771
01:00:44,558 --> 01:00:46,183
They bring in a new rookie,

772
01:00:46,268 --> 01:00:50,479
throw money at him,
buy the car, the house.

773
01:00:50,564 --> 01:00:54,317
After a couple of years,
and your kids are in private schools,

774
01:00:54,401 --> 01:00:57,987
you're used to the good life,
they tell you the truth.

775
01:01:00,198 --> 01:01:01,949
You mean every partner in the Firm is...

776
01:01:02,034 --> 01:01:04,535
Every partner knows.

777
01:01:04,619 --> 01:01:07,163
We suspect most of the associates.

778
01:01:12,085 --> 01:01:16,380
Why don't you get indictments
and bust it all up?

779
01:01:17,299 --> 01:01:20,092
We have to have
somebody on the inside.

780
01:01:20,177 --> 01:01:23,471
We need to see copies of contracts,
clients' bank records,

781
01:01:23,555 --> 01:01:25,681
- articles of incorporation.
- Wait a minute.

782
01:01:25,766 --> 01:01:28,434
- You think I'm...
- You can say no.

783
01:01:28,518 --> 01:01:30,686
But we're gonna break this firm.

784
01:01:30,771 --> 01:01:35,066
And when that happens, you're gonna
go to jail along with the rest.

785
01:01:35,817 --> 01:01:38,235
It will happen, son, believe me.

786
01:01:39,446 --> 01:01:42,031
Why can't I just leave?

787
01:01:42,115 --> 01:01:45,451
That's what Kozinski and Hodges
were trying to do.

788
01:01:47,996 --> 01:01:50,122
You have to think this over.

789
01:01:50,207 --> 01:01:54,418
Meanwhile, you and your wife have to
behave as though everything is normal.

790
01:01:56,630 --> 01:01:58,964
Now don't discuss this with anyone,

791
01:02:00,467 --> 01:02:02,551
but make a decision.

792
01:02:02,636 --> 01:02:06,263
If you help us,
we'll make it worth your while.

793
01:02:06,348 --> 01:02:07,973
Worth my while?

794
01:02:08,058 --> 01:02:10,393
You can still have a pretty good life.

795
01:02:10,477 --> 01:02:14,146
You mean
in a witness protection program?

796
01:02:17,943 --> 01:02:21,445
How? I live somebody else's life?

797
01:02:22,489 --> 01:02:25,825
In some nowhere place, and one day
I'm backing out of my driveway

798
01:02:25,951 --> 01:02:27,743
and my car explodes?

799
01:02:28,662 --> 01:02:31,247
Doesn't have to be that way.

800
01:02:31,331 --> 01:02:35,584
I don't need much of a life, Mr. Voyles,
but it has to be mine.

801
01:02:35,669 --> 01:02:38,254
Is that what you've got now, son?

802
01:02:43,135 --> 01:02:44,760
You ought to get back to the seminar.

803
01:02:44,845 --> 01:02:48,514
Tarrance has full authority
to negotiate on our behalf.

804
01:02:49,683 --> 01:02:52,768
Why don't you wander back
past the memorial?

805
01:03:02,362 --> 01:03:04,447
You can call me in Memphis anytime,
day or night.

806
01:03:04,531 --> 01:03:07,032
The second one's a mobile number.

807
01:03:07,701 --> 01:03:09,452
Let me get this straight.

808
01:03:09,536 --> 01:03:13,289
I steal files from the Firm
and turn them over to the FBI.

809
01:03:13,373 --> 01:03:16,208
Testify against my colleagues,
send them to jail.

810
01:03:16,293 --> 01:03:17,376
They suckered you into this.

811
01:03:17,461 --> 01:03:20,963
Reveal privileged information that
violates attorney-client confidences,

812
01:03:21,047 --> 01:03:24,633
get me disbarred, and then testify
in open court against the Mafia.

813
01:03:24,718 --> 01:03:27,970
- Well, unfortunately, Mitch...
- Let me ask you something.

814
01:03:28,054 --> 01:03:30,639
Are you out of your fucking mind?

815
01:03:31,558 --> 01:03:33,642
How long
before they find out Lomax's cellmate

816
01:03:33,727 --> 01:03:36,061
was a guy named Ray McDeere?

817
01:03:38,315 --> 01:03:41,233
And when they do,
what do you think they'll do to him?

818
01:03:41,318 --> 01:03:43,903
They can get to anyone, anywhere.

819
01:03:44,905 --> 01:03:46,405
What can you do?

820
01:03:46,490 --> 01:03:49,867
Your brother comes up for parole soon,
doesn't he?

821
01:03:50,577 --> 01:03:54,705
You cooperate with us,
I'll guarantee the board will be grateful.

822
01:03:55,707 --> 01:04:00,211
Otherwise... Well, you know
what those parole hearings are like.

823
01:04:01,004 --> 01:04:03,088
It could go either way.

824
01:04:31,284 --> 01:04:33,869
Forget about home, driver.
Take me to the Firm.

825
01:04:33,954 --> 01:04:35,955
- The employer will have...
- Mr. McDeere, you can't go in there!

826
01:04:36,039 --> 01:04:37,706
Call everybody. Right now!

827
01:04:37,791 --> 01:04:41,043
- I'm on overseas and I've got two...
- Right now!

828
01:04:41,127 --> 01:04:43,128
I just had a little chat with the FBI.

829
01:04:49,970 --> 01:04:52,805
- And they didn't try to coerce you?
- No.

830
01:04:54,307 --> 01:04:57,977
- They didn't offer you money?
- Nope.

831
01:04:58,061 --> 01:05:01,313
Did they ask you to contact them again?

832
01:05:01,398 --> 01:05:02,815
What for?

833
01:05:04,985 --> 01:05:07,278
Exactly what did they want?

834
01:05:09,072 --> 01:05:10,823
The secret files.

835
01:05:16,788 --> 01:05:18,831
Who had those secret files last?

836
01:05:18,957 --> 01:05:20,249
You have them, Royce?

837
01:05:20,333 --> 01:05:22,501
- I gave them to you.
- No.

838
01:05:23,503 --> 01:05:27,339
They also suggested that Hodges
and Kozinski were murdered.

839
01:05:29,843 --> 01:05:32,011
Those sons of bitches!

840
01:05:34,139 --> 01:05:38,684
Now, we ought to build a case and sue.
This is pure harassment.

841
01:05:38,768 --> 01:05:40,436
And that was it?

842
01:05:41,771 --> 01:05:44,690
That was everything that was said?

843
01:05:44,774 --> 01:05:47,776
Well, I mean, as far as I can remember.

844
01:05:47,861 --> 01:05:50,279
It wasn't exactly
a sequential conversation.

845
01:05:50,363 --> 01:05:52,448
There was a lot of yelling, mostly by me.

846
01:05:52,532 --> 01:05:57,119
Mitch, we're always doing battle
with the government.

847
01:05:57,203 --> 01:06:01,040
If it isn't the Justice Department,
it's the IRS, and you know what?

848
01:06:01,166 --> 01:06:03,459
We beat them every time.

849
01:06:03,543 --> 01:06:05,961
And they hate us for it.

850
01:06:06,046 --> 01:06:09,715
They can't get to us
so they pick on somebody new.

851
01:06:09,799 --> 01:06:12,718
They invite you to break the law.

852
01:06:12,802 --> 01:06:16,472
Doesn't cost them anything,
but it costs you everything.

853
01:06:18,350 --> 01:06:20,726
Now, I don't want you
to worry about this.

854
01:06:20,810 --> 01:06:24,313
It's gotten serious enough.
We'll have to get into it legally.

855
01:06:24,397 --> 01:06:28,567
I guess the only other question is,
who do we bill this hour to?

856
01:06:31,404 --> 01:06:33,739
How about the FBI?

857
01:07:06,773 --> 01:07:10,275
I can't believe that. That is so weird.

858
01:07:11,111 --> 01:07:13,445
I was just thinking about you.

859
01:07:14,406 --> 01:07:17,282
Somebody's burning leaves outside,
did you smell it?

860
01:07:17,409 --> 01:07:19,702
It reminded me of the time...

861
01:07:25,083 --> 01:07:26,208
Hey!

862
01:07:26,292 --> 01:07:30,087
If you're afraid you'll wake the kids,
we don't have any.

863
01:08:31,691 --> 01:08:48,207
Abby!

864
01:08:48,333 --> 01:08:50,125
- Abby!
- Don't say anything! Don't say anything!

865
01:08:50,210 --> 01:08:52,169
Don't tell me any more!

866
01:08:53,004 --> 01:08:54,463
Everything.

867
01:08:55,215 --> 01:09:00,052
Every single thing we've said
or done since we've been in that house,

868
01:09:01,221 --> 01:09:03,806
nothing has been between us.

869
01:09:03,890 --> 01:09:07,309
Can't we just get in our own car
and drive back to Boston, tonight?

870
01:09:07,393 --> 01:09:09,061
- We'll just leave everything.
- They'd find us.

871
01:09:09,187 --> 01:09:11,396
How do you go to work tomorrow?
How do you look at Avery?

872
01:09:11,481 --> 01:09:12,815
What do you say to him?

873
01:09:12,899 --> 01:09:14,733
I talk about work.

874
01:09:14,859 --> 01:09:17,986
- That's insane!
- I have thought of every possible way.

875
01:09:18,071 --> 01:09:20,989
Here, in the Caymans, in Washington,
that's all I've done.

876
01:09:21,074 --> 01:09:25,828
Try to think of a way out. If we run,
they'd find us, and it gets Ray killed.

877
01:09:25,912 --> 01:09:28,247
- But if you testify...
- The FBI says they'll help Ray

878
01:09:28,331 --> 01:09:30,749
- and protect us.
- Protect what?

879
01:09:34,087 --> 01:09:36,421
What are you going to do?

880
01:09:37,757 --> 01:09:40,592
Go in tomorrow and start to copy files.

881
01:09:40,718 --> 01:09:42,219
I don't have a choice.

882
01:09:42,303 --> 01:09:44,555
Mitch,

883
01:09:44,639 --> 01:09:46,682
what are you saying?

884
01:09:46,766 --> 01:09:48,767
You'll be revealing clients' secrets.

885
01:09:48,893 --> 01:09:50,310
- You'll be disbarred.
- Abby, don't...

886
01:09:50,436 --> 01:09:53,105
You'll never be able to practice
law again for the rest of your life.

887
01:09:53,231 --> 01:09:56,400
Everything you've worked for!
They can't ask you to do that!

888
01:09:56,484 --> 01:09:58,443
They are not asking!

889
01:10:06,119 --> 01:10:10,289
We have to behave
exactly as we have been.

890
01:10:11,416 --> 01:10:15,502
We have to go to work
and come home every day

891
01:10:16,254 --> 01:10:20,090
and never wonder about the walls
and the wires...

892
01:10:20,174 --> 01:10:22,467
And do nothing we want to do.

893
01:10:37,275 --> 01:10:39,651
Szechwan beef from Wong Boys.

894
01:10:40,528 --> 01:10:43,488
That was the last time
I remember laughing.

895
01:10:44,949 --> 01:10:47,534
- Come on! Every single day we got...
- Oh, not you again, man.

896
01:10:47,660 --> 01:10:49,411
...one of your trucks out here,
blocking this alley.

897
01:10:49,495 --> 01:10:51,121
- Hey, leave me alone.
- What's it gonna take, huh?

898
01:10:51,205 --> 01:10:52,414
Hey, would you leave me alone, buddy?

899
01:10:52,498 --> 01:10:54,625
You're using this place as a parking lot!

900
01:11:32,997 --> 01:11:35,624
What the hell are you doing?

901
01:11:35,708 --> 01:11:38,418
Jesus, I was just trying
to make a copy of...

902
01:11:38,544 --> 01:11:43,131
They just started this. You have to have
the billing code for each client.

903
01:11:43,216 --> 01:11:45,801
You mean every time
I copy a piece of paper, it's recorded?

904
01:11:45,885 --> 01:11:47,594
What are you trying to do, kill yourself?

905
01:11:47,720 --> 01:11:50,389
Come on. Nina should do that anyway.

906
01:11:51,349 --> 01:11:54,017
Come down for one night, can't you?

907
01:11:55,561 --> 01:11:57,896
Well, it used to be worth it.

908
01:12:01,234 --> 01:12:05,404
Okay. Yeah, maybe next time.

909
01:12:06,072 --> 01:12:07,781
Bye, Cordelia.

910
01:12:09,075 --> 01:12:10,325
That was Cordelia.

911
01:12:10,410 --> 01:12:12,577
Yeah. Your wife.

912
01:12:12,912 --> 01:12:14,329
From the song of the same name.

913
01:12:14,414 --> 01:12:17,499
Avery, I have a couple of ideas
about those Capps LCs.

914
01:12:17,583 --> 01:12:19,876
When's the next Cayman trip?

915
01:12:20,586 --> 01:12:22,838
For me? Next week.

916
01:12:22,922 --> 01:12:26,633
If you think I'm gonna let Sonny Capps
get another look at you, you're crazy.

917
01:12:26,759 --> 01:12:28,301
But you write down
every single thought you have.

918
01:12:28,428 --> 01:12:30,762
I'll be happy to take credit.

919
01:12:32,765 --> 01:12:37,269
Mr. McDeere! Mr. Mulholland's
called twice about his bills again.

920
01:12:37,395 --> 01:12:40,355
Tell Mr. Mulholland to take his bill and...

921
01:12:40,440 --> 01:12:42,733
No, wait a minute, wait a minute.
Isn't he just up the street?

922
01:12:42,817 --> 01:12:44,735
- Yes. In the Cotton Exchange.
- Cotton Exchange.

923
01:12:44,819 --> 01:12:46,862
Tell him I'll see him later.

924
01:12:46,946 --> 01:12:49,865
Did you order a fried egg sandwich
from the Front Street Deli?

925
01:12:49,949 --> 01:12:51,742
A fried egg...

926
01:12:57,415 --> 01:12:59,499
Yes, I did. I did.

927
01:13:00,835 --> 01:13:02,294
Come in.

928
01:13:04,589 --> 01:13:07,591
It's $2.65. The receipt's in the bag.

929
01:13:14,766 --> 01:13:16,808
The receipt's in the bag.

930
01:13:36,454 --> 01:13:38,872
How did you see them,
and they didn't see you?

931
01:13:38,998 --> 01:13:40,874
I was under the desk.

932
01:13:45,046 --> 01:13:48,882
I was vacuuming the rug.
You want me to draw you a diagram?

933
01:13:50,551 --> 01:13:52,052
I loved him.

934
01:13:54,180 --> 01:13:55,847
I'm sorry, Tammy.

935
01:13:59,060 --> 01:14:00,185
They wanted to know who hired him

936
01:14:00,311 --> 01:14:03,730
and why he was asking questions
about dead lawyers.

937
01:14:08,653 --> 01:14:10,570
You actually saw them?

938
01:14:13,324 --> 01:14:16,868
One guy was stocky,
looked like a wrestler.

939
01:14:17,662 --> 01:14:20,205
He's gonna limp the rest of his life

940
01:14:20,331 --> 01:14:24,501
'cause Eddie hit him in the knee
with that cannon under his desk.

941
01:14:25,545 --> 01:14:28,713
And the other guy was like an albino.

942
01:14:31,050 --> 01:14:34,928
Long thin hair, almost white.

943
01:14:35,555 --> 01:14:37,222
Dead blue eyes.

944
01:14:39,725 --> 01:14:41,685
My landlady said
they came looking for me yesterday,

945
01:14:41,769 --> 01:14:43,478
so I checked into the Motel 6
on River Street.

946
01:14:43,563 --> 01:14:46,439
I couldn't think of anywhere else to go.

947
01:14:49,569 --> 01:14:53,697
Listen, they're gonna put Eddie
together with Ray, and when they do,

948
01:14:54,407 --> 01:14:56,241
it'll lead to you.

949
01:14:57,702 --> 01:15:00,078
I don't want anything bad
to happen to you.

950
01:15:00,204 --> 01:15:02,289
Eddie wouldn't like it.

951
01:15:02,415 --> 01:15:05,208
So, you're in as much trouble as I am.

952
01:15:06,586 --> 01:15:10,714
Listen, there's a building around
the corner called the Cotton Exchange.

953
01:15:10,798 --> 01:15:12,299
Maybe you can help, Tammy.

954
01:15:16,304 --> 01:15:17,554
Hi there, Mitch.

955
01:15:17,638 --> 01:15:20,515
Bill Devasher, Firm Security.

956
01:15:20,600 --> 01:15:25,061
Mr. Locke and Mr. Lambert were telling
me about your little run in with the FBI.

957
01:15:25,146 --> 01:15:27,856
I wonder if we could have a little talk.

958
01:15:27,940 --> 01:15:29,941
Actually, I told them everything.

959
01:15:30,067 --> 01:15:32,986
I'm sure you did.
This won't take a minute.

960
01:15:40,620 --> 01:15:41,995
Hop in.

961
01:16:12,276 --> 01:16:14,653
So, Mitch, this is a debriefing.

962
01:16:18,324 --> 01:16:20,951
I know pretty much
what you told the fellows,

963
01:16:21,035 --> 01:16:23,328
so I kind of got the picture.

964
01:16:23,454 --> 01:16:26,289
Now it's my job to give you the picture.

965
01:16:26,374 --> 01:16:29,167
What I'm concerned about, son, is this.

966
01:16:29,293 --> 01:16:32,128
The FBI wouldn't have come after you
if they didn't figure they'd get to you.

967
01:16:32,213 --> 01:16:34,381
What do you suppose
made them think that?

968
01:16:34,507 --> 01:16:35,882
I have no idea.

969
01:16:36,008 --> 01:16:38,843
Well, see, it's my job
to have an idea about that.

970
01:16:38,970 --> 01:16:42,389
For example, they might know
how important your young wife is to you.

971
01:16:42,515 --> 01:16:44,349
They might use that.

972
01:16:45,393 --> 01:16:46,685
How?

973
01:16:47,853 --> 01:16:51,773
Avery says last Friday
you took the afternoon off.

974
01:16:51,857 --> 01:16:55,235
He figures you might have been
with another woman.

975
01:16:56,362 --> 01:16:57,487
- Why would Avery think...
- How do you know

976
01:16:57,571 --> 01:16:59,030
you weren't followed?

977
01:17:03,703 --> 01:17:07,497
Picture Abby one day
walking to the mail box,

978
01:17:07,581 --> 01:17:12,210
anticipating the arrival of her Redbook,
her Sharper lmage catalog.

979
01:17:13,504 --> 01:17:15,714
What does she find instead?

980
01:17:16,590 --> 01:17:18,758
She finds heartache, Mitch.

981
01:17:19,719 --> 01:17:21,219
The death of love and trust.

982
01:17:22,430 --> 01:17:25,056
Imagine her one day opening that.

983
01:17:25,182 --> 01:17:27,225
Go ahead. Take a look.

984
01:17:31,063 --> 01:17:32,564
Devastating.

985
01:17:37,695 --> 01:17:39,779
Not just screwing, Mitch.

986
01:17:41,615 --> 01:17:45,702
But the kind of intimate acts,
oral and whatnot,

987
