01:37:53,034 --> 01:37:55,452
You're taller than I thought.

1230
01:37:55,537 --> 01:37:57,955
That's nice to hear.

1231
01:37:58,081 --> 01:38:00,415
There's been a change of plan.

1232
01:38:01,376 --> 01:38:03,710
I didn't know there was a plan.

1233
01:38:03,795 --> 01:38:06,255
Good, because it's been changed.

1234
01:38:07,131 --> 01:38:08,966
Who are you, sweetheart?

1235
01:38:15,056 --> 01:38:16,640
Abanks' Diving Lodge.

1236
01:38:16,724 --> 01:38:18,642
What time
has Avery chartered the boat for?

1237
01:38:18,768 --> 01:38:20,060
2:30.

1238
01:38:20,812 --> 01:38:24,231
Okay, now, you got to keep him out long
enough to copy everything in that closet.

1239
01:38:24,315 --> 01:38:26,483
Don't worry. My friends are taking him
to Trinity Caves.

1240
01:38:26,609 --> 01:38:28,569
- It should be a good six hours.
- Okay.

1241
01:38:28,653 --> 01:38:31,822
Tammy's coming down tomorrow
to set things up.

1242
01:38:45,420 --> 01:38:48,463
I can... I can whip us up some eggs.

1243
01:38:49,757 --> 01:38:53,010
Last day,
I don't want to be late for school.

1244
01:39:00,310 --> 01:39:02,269
Has Tammy left to meet Abanks?

1245
01:39:02,353 --> 01:39:04,354
Not until this evening.

1246
01:39:07,483 --> 01:39:10,777
You're running a real 3-ring circus,
aren't you?

1247
01:39:13,531 --> 01:39:15,949
- I hope it goes well.
- It has to.

1248
01:39:20,788 --> 01:39:22,873
You know, isn't it amazing?

1249
01:39:23,833 --> 01:39:27,794
You did the cheating,
and I'm the one who feels guilty.

1250
01:39:27,879 --> 01:39:29,129
Don't.

1251
01:39:38,389 --> 01:39:40,515
Take care of yourself.

1252
01:39:47,231 --> 01:39:50,233
Hey! Hey! Stop that!

1253
01:39:50,318 --> 01:39:51,401
Where are your gloves?

1254
01:39:51,486 --> 01:39:54,821
Get back to the dodge ball game.
You, too, Sheila.

1255
01:40:05,833 --> 01:40:09,211
Boys and girls together,
rehearsing for later life.

1256
01:40:09,921 --> 01:40:11,421
What are you doing here?

1257
01:40:11,547 --> 01:40:14,174
Would you believe I just happened to be
in the neighborhood?

1258
01:40:14,258 --> 01:40:15,425
No.

1259
01:40:16,594 --> 01:40:19,012
I heard this was your last day.

1260
01:40:19,931 --> 01:40:21,682
Was I misinformed?

1261
01:40:23,559 --> 01:40:25,018
I'll be gone for a while.

1262
01:40:25,103 --> 01:40:27,854
I just stopped off to say goodbye.

1263
01:40:27,939 --> 01:40:30,273
- Just in case.
- In case what?

1264
01:40:31,275 --> 01:40:34,194
In case it's more than a while.

1265
01:40:34,278 --> 01:40:38,573
I'm going to the Caymans tomorrow,
and I would miss saying goodbye.

1266
01:40:40,368 --> 01:40:43,370
Well, thank you. Have a nice trip.

1267
01:40:43,454 --> 01:40:44,788
Want to come?

1268
01:40:44,914 --> 01:40:49,626
I know. I know, it sounds outrageous,

1269
01:40:50,253 --> 01:40:51,586
but think about it.

1270
01:40:52,797 --> 01:40:58,051
We could grab some sun, take a dip,
drink some Havana Club.

1271
01:40:59,303 --> 01:41:02,639
I could give you marital advice
and hit on you,

1272
01:41:03,725 --> 01:41:07,310
and whatever happens,
I promise I take rejection well.

1273
01:41:09,147 --> 01:41:11,481
What makes you think
I need marital advice?

1274
01:41:11,607 --> 01:41:14,109
Okay, you give me marital advice.

1275
01:41:16,320 --> 01:41:18,405
I couldn't possibly.

1276
01:41:19,782 --> 01:41:23,577
- I don't scuba dive.
- Perfect. I can't scuba dive either.

1277
01:41:23,661 --> 01:41:24,995
Really?

1278
01:41:26,330 --> 01:41:28,331
I'd heard that
you don't miss a chance to...

1279
01:41:28,458 --> 01:41:29,833
Not this time.

1280
01:41:29,959 --> 01:41:32,753
I had to shorten the trip,
clients coming into town.

1281
01:41:32,837 --> 01:41:36,423
I can't dive and fly in the same 24 hours.
So, you see?

1282
01:41:37,508 --> 01:41:39,342
How about it?

1283
01:41:40,845 --> 01:41:42,846
My mother isn't well.

1284
01:41:44,432 --> 01:41:46,516
They're doing some tests.

1285
01:41:47,018 --> 01:41:49,686
That's why I'm going home.

1286
01:41:50,021 --> 01:41:52,147
I'm sorry. I didn't know.

1287
01:41:53,024 --> 01:41:55,108
How could you possibly?

1288
01:41:56,360 --> 01:42:01,323
I hope she feels better,
and if she does, bring her with you.

1289
01:42:04,702 --> 01:42:08,038
Goodbye, Avery. Have a good flight.

1290
01:42:17,632 --> 01:42:19,382
Greenwood Secretarial Services.

1291
01:42:19,509 --> 01:42:22,719
Tammy, this is Abby McDeere.
I think you've got a serious problem.

1292
01:42:22,804 --> 01:42:24,846
Avery's not going diving.

1293
01:42:26,724 --> 01:42:28,225
We're dead.

1294
01:42:31,229 --> 01:42:33,230
Well, how do we...

1295
01:42:35,691 --> 01:42:37,901
How am I gonna tell Mitch?
How am I gonna let him know?

1296
01:42:46,410 --> 01:42:49,329
I'm going anyway.
I've got to try to do something.

1297
01:42:49,413 --> 01:42:51,873
My flight's in three hours.

1298
01:42:58,589 --> 01:43:00,257
Mr. McDeere's office.

1299
01:43:00,883 --> 01:43:02,759
I'm sorry, he's not in.
May I take a message?

1300
01:43:20,111 --> 01:43:22,612
Tammy, don't tell Mitch anything.

1301
01:43:26,784 --> 01:43:28,702
I'll just be a sec.

1302
01:43:30,121 --> 01:43:32,747
A prescription for Abigail McDeere.

1303
01:43:49,307 --> 01:43:50,640
One!

1304
01:43:54,061 --> 01:43:57,147
Well, you want to go,
or do you want to stay here?

1305
01:43:57,231 --> 01:44:00,650
- Aren't you gonna cuff him?
- I'll take care of it.

1306
01:44:12,747 --> 01:44:14,247
Yeah?

1307
01:44:14,332 --> 01:44:16,499
Guess what I'm looking at?

1308
01:44:17,919 --> 01:44:19,252
Tell me.

1309
01:44:19,795 --> 01:44:22,339
My first sunset in six years.

1310
01:44:24,508 --> 01:44:26,343
- You made it.
- Yeah.

1311
01:44:27,511 --> 01:44:29,262
Yeah, I did.

1312
01:44:29,347 --> 01:44:31,514
I owe you, little brother.

1313
01:44:33,351 --> 01:44:34,935
No, you don't.

1314
01:44:37,772 --> 01:44:41,024
- Anything from Abanks?
- Last I heard, everything was set.

1315
01:44:42,026 --> 01:44:43,944
It's gonna be fine.

1316
01:44:45,279 --> 01:44:46,863
It already is.

1317
01:44:50,451 --> 01:44:52,285
I'll be seeing you, Ray.

1318
01:44:54,038 --> 01:44:56,790
Okay, you spoke to him.
Now, where are the files?

1319
01:44:56,874 --> 01:44:58,124
Where's the money?

1320
01:44:58,209 --> 01:44:59,709
Not until I get the files.

1321
01:44:59,794 --> 01:45:01,544
You send half now.

1322
01:45:01,671 --> 01:45:05,799
Account number 6194408S.
You got that?

1323
01:45:06,300 --> 01:45:10,387
Yeah. 6194408S, yeah.

1324
01:45:11,180 --> 01:45:14,975
When I get confirmation it's there,
I'll send the files.

1325
01:45:23,234 --> 01:45:25,568
Here's some pocket money.

1326
01:45:25,695 --> 01:45:29,322
You're free, McDeere.
There's a bus stop a quarter mile.

1327
01:45:29,407 --> 01:45:32,409
Follow the yellow line.
You're used to that.

1328
01:46:19,165 --> 01:46:20,832
Excuse me.

1329
01:46:39,643 --> 01:46:42,187
You don't seem that surprised.

1330
01:46:42,271 --> 01:46:44,189
I'm deeply surprised.

1331
01:46:46,067 --> 01:46:47,358
So am I.

1332
01:46:59,538 --> 01:47:01,664
Stephanie, could we have
two Havana Club, please?

1333
01:47:01,749 --> 01:47:03,333
Yes, Mr. Tolar.

1334
01:47:18,015 --> 01:47:20,350
How'd the test turn out?

1335
01:47:20,434 --> 01:47:23,061
We were worried for no reason.

1336
01:47:23,187 --> 01:47:24,354
Good.

1337
01:47:26,524 --> 01:47:30,193
I didn't think we'd got on that well
in the school yard.

1338
01:47:31,695 --> 01:47:34,280
Maybe I've grown up since then.

1339
01:47:34,365 --> 01:47:36,449
I'd love to believe that.

1340
01:47:55,553 --> 01:47:57,887
- It's delicious.
- Isn't it?

1341
01:47:57,972 --> 01:47:59,722
It's like cognac.

1342
01:48:01,600 --> 01:48:04,394
You know, I have a very bad reputation.

1343
01:48:07,773 --> 01:48:10,150
- What do you do?
- I run around.

1344
01:48:11,443 --> 01:48:13,278
Why do you do that?

1345
01:48:16,240 --> 01:48:19,242
I think it's because
my wife understands me.

1346
01:48:24,248 --> 01:48:26,416
The fact is, I love my wife.

1347
01:48:30,421 --> 01:48:34,090
But she's... Well,
I guess she's lost interest in me.

1348
01:48:34,800 --> 01:48:36,426
I know I have.

1349
01:48:40,306 --> 01:48:43,683
And I haven't cared for anyone since.

1350
01:48:46,604 --> 01:48:48,438
I'd like to, though.

1351
01:48:49,815 --> 01:48:51,191
I miss it.

1352
01:48:56,864 --> 01:48:59,991
My, you lay a lot on a girl for a first date.

1353
01:49:01,619 --> 01:49:03,453
Is that what this is?

1354
01:49:12,713 --> 01:49:13,755
This is Unit B.

1355
01:49:13,839 --> 01:49:17,884
We'll be pulling into Five Points
at 11: 15 for a 20-minute rest stop.

1356
01:49:17,968 --> 01:49:19,969
Mrs. Sunderland,
I'm sorry to call you at home so late,

1357
01:49:20,054 --> 01:49:23,056
but I need to speak to you
about something that's, well,

1358
01:49:23,140 --> 01:49:24,682
it's really quite embarrassing.

1359
01:49:24,808 --> 01:49:27,352
Let me preface this by saying
you're not the only client at the Firm

1360
01:49:27,478 --> 01:49:28,561
that I've had to call about this.

1361
01:50:40,467 --> 01:50:43,886
I'd like a big steak, medium rare,
three fried eggs over,

1362
01:50:43,971 --> 01:50:46,389
French fries and coffee, please.

1363
01:50:50,894 --> 01:50:53,479
I'll see you, darling.

1364
01:52:03,092 --> 01:52:04,467
Fuck!

1365
01:52:21,527 --> 01:52:23,945
What the hell is going on?
We lost your brother.

1366
01:52:24,029 --> 01:52:26,197
Why, were you following him?

1367
01:52:26,323 --> 01:52:28,282
Are you trying to fuck with me?

1368
01:52:28,367 --> 01:52:29,784
Where are you? Where are those files?

1369
01:52:29,868 --> 01:52:33,329
Are you trying to fuck with me?
You want the files, you wire the money.

1370
01:52:33,455 --> 01:52:34,997
I want those files now.

1371
01:52:35,124 --> 01:52:36,958
Got to go, Wayne.

1372
01:52:39,336 --> 01:52:42,130
He knows exactly where his brother is.

1373
01:52:43,215 --> 01:52:44,715
Have them check all the credit cards

1374
01:52:44,842 --> 01:52:48,386
of everybody that got fuel outside
that diner between 11:00 and 11:45,

1375
01:52:48,512 --> 01:52:50,763
whenever we lost Ray.

1376
01:52:50,848 --> 01:52:52,140
There couldn't be
more than a dozen or so.

1377
01:52:52,224 --> 01:52:54,142
He's got to be on one of them.

1378
01:52:54,226 --> 01:52:56,561
And get me a map of Louisiana.

1379
01:52:58,355 --> 01:53:00,356
Get me a map of Louisiana!

1380
01:53:38,395 --> 01:53:40,563
It hasn't even begun to melt.

1381
01:53:41,523 --> 01:53:44,108
The staff was chosen for its timing.

1382
01:54:35,577 --> 01:54:38,496
I would do that,
but I could never do that.

1383
01:54:39,957 --> 01:54:42,124
The buttons are too small.

1384
01:54:44,086 --> 01:54:46,587
It requires terrible...

1385
01:54:46,672 --> 01:54:48,172
Dexterity.

1386
01:54:50,926 --> 01:54:52,635
Amazing.

1387
01:55:04,481 --> 01:55:06,107
What are you doing here?

1388
01:55:06,191 --> 01:55:07,817
What do you mean?

1389
01:55:07,943 --> 01:55:10,570
I mean,
exactly what did you come here for?

1390
01:55:10,654 --> 01:55:12,822
I thought I was invited.

1391
01:55:13,198 --> 01:55:15,366
You're not being truthful.

1392
01:55:17,494 --> 01:55:19,996
Why are you doing this?

1393
01:55:20,330 --> 01:55:25,042
Because I'm sick
and I want you to tell me the truth.

1394
01:55:27,004 --> 01:55:31,173
I came here to punish Mitch
for letting the Firm ruin our lives.

1395
01:55:32,509 --> 01:55:36,137
I came because when Mitch was here
with you he slept with someone else.

1396
01:55:36,221 --> 01:55:38,556
Is that what you want to hear?

1397
01:55:44,688 --> 01:55:47,315
That's better than the alternative.

1398
01:55:48,025 --> 01:55:49,775
What alternative?

1399
01:55:50,819 --> 01:55:53,154
That you came here to see me.

1400
01:56:21,224 --> 01:56:22,475
Avery?

1401
01:56:57,678 --> 01:56:59,929
It came in about three hours ago.

1402
01:57:00,013 --> 01:57:01,681
You sure he'll be all right?

1403
01:57:01,765 --> 01:57:03,933
What the hell you want to do? Call 911?

1404
01:57:04,017 --> 01:57:07,520
Get the key,
grab the stuff and get over here.

1405
01:57:07,604 --> 01:57:09,105
Keep calling him.

1406
01:57:09,189 --> 01:57:12,274
Wake the son of a bitch up. When you
get him on the phone, find me.

1407
01:57:12,401 --> 01:57:13,442
I want that girl.

1408
01:57:19,282 --> 01:57:23,536
The account number is 6194408S.

1409
01:57:25,122 --> 01:57:28,457
And can you confirm that it is $750,000?

1410
01:57:49,146 --> 01:57:52,273
Absolutely. I'm fixing
to get out of here now.

1411
01:57:53,066 --> 01:57:54,567
You got all the information I need?

1412
01:57:54,651 --> 01:57:57,903
Yeah, but, Mitch...

1413
01:57:57,988 --> 01:58:02,158
I've been looking at this stuff
and there's no numbers listed.

1414
01:58:02,242 --> 01:58:04,493
There's no numbers? No amounts?

1415
01:58:04,578 --> 01:58:06,579
No, I got papers
for bank accounts everywhere

1416
01:58:06,663 --> 01:58:10,166
from the Caymans to Hong Kong,
but there's no amounts.

1417
01:58:12,127 --> 01:58:14,587
I can't play the poker game
I'm gonna play and bluff.

1418
01:58:14,671 --> 01:58:17,173
I gotta know
how much they have and where.

1419
01:58:17,257 --> 01:58:20,176
There's a note on each one that says,

1420
01:58:21,011 --> 01:58:24,513
"Info held by client and my Mac.
Signed A.T."

1421
01:58:24,639 --> 01:58:27,516
Is there any other information?
Is there a password?

1422
01:58:27,642 --> 01:58:30,019
Some kind of password?
Just look on the paper, Tammy.

1423
01:58:30,103 --> 01:58:31,771
Wait a minute.

1424
01:58:31,855 --> 01:58:35,107
On the side of one,
in parenthesis it says,

1425
01:58:35,192 --> 01:58:39,695
"R-E-F," then a colon, then, "Cordelia."

1426
01:58:40,447 --> 01:58:43,365
Okay, okay, I've got to get to Avery's
computer in the morning before I leave.

1427
01:58:43,492 --> 01:58:44,784
Well, listen, be careful.

1428
01:58:44,868 --> 01:58:47,286
We don't know how this is
all gonna look in the morning.

1429
01:58:47,370 --> 01:58:49,538
I should be able
to get through the morning fine.

1430
01:58:49,664 --> 01:58:52,374
By the time they notice I'm not
back from lunch, I'll be in Chicago.

1431
01:59:00,842 --> 01:59:03,636
Okay. We're finished. That's it.
I gotta get these out to the boat.

1432
01:59:03,720 --> 01:59:05,346
The boat?

1433
01:59:06,139 --> 01:59:07,973
- What boat?
- Oh, man.

1434
01:59:09,351 --> 01:59:11,977
Later on there's some stuff I gotta
tell you about what Mitch is doing.

1435
01:59:12,062 --> 01:59:13,395
Tell me now, Tammy. What?

1436
01:59:13,480 --> 01:59:16,649
Get the damn keys back in his pants
and get out of there before he wakes up.

1437
01:59:36,253 --> 01:59:37,795
Hello?

1438
01:59:42,300 --> 01:59:44,552
You have to repeat that.

1439
01:59:48,849 --> 01:59:50,266
That's not possible.

1440
01:59:50,350 --> 01:59:53,352
She stole your keys
and God knows what else.

1441
01:59:53,979 --> 01:59:56,063
Now who the hell is she?

1442
01:59:56,147 --> 01:59:59,108
You know me,

1443
01:59:59,192 --> 02:00:01,485
just somebody I met last night.

1444
02:00:01,570 --> 02:00:04,280
Then how the hell does she know
to go after your keys?

1445
02:00:04,364 --> 02:00:07,950
The guys will be landing in about
10 minutes and she better be there.

1446
02:00:40,734 --> 02:00:41,942
Don't.

1447
02:00:44,154 --> 02:00:46,405
They heard you on the phone.

1448
02:00:50,994 --> 02:00:52,620
Mitch sent you.

1449
02:00:57,584 --> 02:00:59,835
I knew he was a closet idealist.

1450
02:00:59,920 --> 02:01:02,004
He doesn't know I'm here.

1451
02:01:03,965 --> 02:01:06,050
But I did do it for him.

1452
02:01:06,760 --> 02:01:09,887
That's even better
than getting even with him.

1453
02:01:12,515 --> 02:01:14,266
You gotta get out of here.

1454
02:01:21,358 --> 02:01:23,067
What are you going to do?

1455
02:01:23,151 --> 02:01:25,527
Abby, the girl was a set-up.

1456
02:01:27,280 --> 02:01:29,698
On the beach, she was a set-up.

1457
02:01:32,661 --> 02:01:34,787
They do things like that.

1458
02:01:35,455 --> 02:01:38,582
Just in case
the usual inducements don't work.

1459
02:01:41,044 --> 02:01:44,129
What's going to happen?
What are they going to do to you?

1460
02:01:44,214 --> 02:01:46,173
Whatever it is...

1461
02:01:48,760 --> 02:01:50,803
They did it a long time ago.

1462
02:01:52,681 --> 02:01:54,014
Get this thing out of here, will you?

1463
02:01:54,099 --> 02:01:56,308
Look, this ain't your cotton truck,
and this ain't your alley!

1464
02:01:56,393 --> 02:01:58,602
I'm calling in to
the Department of Traffic right now!

1465
02:01:58,687 --> 02:01:59,895
They call?

1466
02:01:59,980 --> 02:02:01,438
Not yet.

1467
02:02:05,652 --> 02:02:07,528
Madge, I just talked to Avery
in the Caymans.

1468
02:02:07,612 --> 02:02:09,780
He needs some work done
on the Kemmer papers before 10:00.

1469
02:02:09,864 --> 02:02:12,032
I'll just get it off his computer.

1470
02:02:17,163 --> 02:02:18,414
What the hell's
the matter with you guys?

1471
02:02:18,498 --> 02:02:20,666
This thing's out of paper.

1472
02:02:37,976 --> 02:02:39,351
McDeere in yet?

1473
02:02:39,436 --> 02:02:41,729
Check every goddamn floor
and find him.

1474
02:02:41,813 --> 02:02:43,522
That son of a bitch cut a deal.

