1595
02:17:50,012 --> 02:17:51,638
Stay in Chicago, Maury.

1596
02:17:51,722 --> 02:17:54,223
This kid's cut a deal
and I bet it's a beaut.

1597
02:17:54,350 --> 02:17:57,143
If I get my hands on this fucking kid,
Joey, if I get my hands on this kid...

1598
02:17:57,227 --> 02:17:59,020
- Excuse me.
- Not now, Ruthie.

1599
02:17:59,104 --> 02:18:01,397
I think it's urgent, Mr. Morolto.

1600
02:18:01,523 --> 02:18:03,107
Ruthie thinks it's urgent.
What do you think, Joey?

1601
02:18:03,192 --> 02:18:05,026
It's a Mr. McDeere.

1602
02:18:05,694 --> 02:18:07,528
Mr. Mitchell McDeere.

1603
02:18:08,864 --> 02:18:10,907
He's waiting to see you.

1604
02:18:12,743 --> 02:18:14,744
I think Ruth is right.

1605
02:18:39,395 --> 02:18:40,853
I'm Mitch McDeere.

1606
02:18:42,731 --> 02:18:45,024
I'm your attorney.

1607
02:18:45,776 --> 02:18:47,694
One of them, anyway.

1608
02:18:48,696 --> 02:18:52,573
I assume you knew,
but I thought I'd mention it, in case.

1609
02:18:55,202 --> 02:18:58,121
- Would you care to sit down?
- Not really.

1610
02:18:59,581 --> 02:19:02,709
I want to try and...

1611
02:19:06,755 --> 02:19:10,717
This is just... This is very awkward.

1612
02:19:13,262 --> 02:19:17,515
I'm afraid my firm has behaved

1613
02:19:17,599 --> 02:19:19,976
in an unethical manner.

1614
02:19:21,979 --> 02:19:24,814
It seems that we,
Bendini, Lambert & Locke,

1615
02:19:24,940 --> 02:19:27,442
the entire firm, has been engaged in a...

1616
02:19:28,902 --> 02:19:31,112
Well, a conspiracy.

1617
02:19:33,115 --> 02:19:36,367
We've been

1618
02:19:36,452 --> 02:19:38,911
overbilling our clients.

1619
02:19:54,845 --> 02:19:57,472
In some cases, massive overbilling.

1620
02:19:58,974 --> 02:20:03,811
I assure you I had no idea any of this
was going on when I joined the Firm.

1621
02:20:03,937 --> 02:20:07,273
Well, I feel I have to report
this criminal behavior.

1622
02:20:08,650 --> 02:20:10,485
But I can't use...

1623
02:20:10,611 --> 02:20:15,615
I can't use your invoices
without your written authorization.

1624
02:20:15,699 --> 02:20:17,992
- Our invoices?
- Tony, please.

1625
02:20:18,952 --> 02:20:20,203
Listen.

1626
02:20:20,329 --> 02:20:21,454
Yes, sir. Your bills.

1627
02:20:21,538 --> 02:20:25,750
You see, it's an important part
of the proof that we've overbilled you.

1628
02:20:27,336 --> 02:20:28,711
That's it?

1629
02:20:30,506 --> 02:20:32,715
Pretty much.

1630
02:20:32,841 --> 02:20:36,886
Well, most of our clients
have already agreed, pretty much all.

1631
02:20:37,012 --> 02:20:39,764
Except for you. Which is why I'm here.

1632
02:20:41,391 --> 02:20:45,019
And this is what
you've been talking to the FBI about?

1633
02:20:46,605 --> 02:20:48,856
You want us to let you turn our bills...

1634
02:20:48,941 --> 02:20:52,902
What we charged you,
I should say overcharged you.

1635
02:20:53,028 --> 02:20:55,863
...over to the government.
- Yes, sir.

1636
02:20:55,948 --> 02:20:57,990
- Now, does that in any way...
- No, sir.

1637
02:20:58,075 --> 02:21:02,703
It does not in any way waive your rights
to full and complete confidentiality

1638
02:21:02,788 --> 02:21:06,374
in any other area
of the attorney-client relationship.

1639
02:21:08,877 --> 02:21:10,753
I'm your lawyer, gentlemen.

1640
02:21:12,214 --> 02:21:15,174
Whether I like it or not, I can't talk
to the government about you

1641
02:21:15,259 --> 02:21:17,885
even when I'm no longer your lawyer.

1642
02:21:19,555 --> 02:21:22,431
That would be breaking my word,
my oath.

1643
02:21:23,058 --> 02:21:24,725
All right, Mitch.

1644
02:21:25,769 --> 02:21:28,271
So what was this stealing of the files?

1645
02:21:28,397 --> 02:21:30,898
What the fuck was this all about?

1646
02:21:30,983 --> 02:21:33,276
The files haven't been stolen.

1647
02:21:33,402 --> 02:21:36,404
They're in exactly the same place
they were.

1648
02:21:37,239 --> 02:21:40,158
I just felt it was important for me
to be thoroughly familiar

1649
02:21:40,242 --> 02:21:42,743
with the precise make-up
and whereabouts

1650
02:21:42,828 --> 02:21:45,580
of all your holdings and activities.

1651
02:21:46,957 --> 02:21:50,293
So I prepared copies of everything.

1652
02:21:53,505 --> 02:21:55,798
That way you and I
can communicate perfectly,

1653
02:21:55,924 --> 02:21:59,677
and, of course,
if we ever have to talk to a third party,

1654
02:22:01,263 --> 02:22:02,972
then I know everything,

1655
02:22:03,098 --> 02:22:07,435
right down to the penny, pound,
franc and deutsche mark.

1656
02:22:08,854 --> 02:22:11,564
I know everything you know.

1657
02:22:11,648 --> 02:22:14,275
As I should, as your attorney.

1658
02:22:16,403 --> 02:22:20,198
And what if the Firm
should desire at some point

1659
02:22:20,282 --> 02:22:22,283
to terminate your employment?

1660
02:22:22,367 --> 02:22:28,789
Whatever I know, wherever I go, I am
bound by the attorney-client privilege.

1661
02:22:29,917 --> 02:22:32,126
I am very much like...

1662
02:22:33,795 --> 02:22:36,214
I would say I am exactly like

1663
02:22:37,591 --> 02:22:41,219
a ship carrying a cargo
that will never reach any port.

1664
02:22:43,305 --> 02:22:48,851
